gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Cavaliers 113, Timberwolves 104
gameRecap.excerpt: The Cavaliers outscored the Wolves 16-7 in OT as they defeated them, 113-104. Darius Garland led the Cavaliers with 34 points, four rebounds, and eight assists as Jarrett Allen added a career-high 33 points and 18 rebounds. Naz Reid led the Wolves with a career-high 34 points, along with five rebounds and two blocks while Anthony Edwards had 19 points on 7-27 FG. The Cavs move to 41-22 as the Wolves go to 44-20. With the loss, Minnesota moves to the #2 seed in the West as OKC is now a half game up with their win over Miami tonight.
